This was definitely the highlight of 2022 for me. Being able to drive a hummer completely underwater with a SCUBA mask across a lake! And to do it all in my own backyard is really just my wildest dreams coming true. I’m so thankful for all my friends who helped me make this happen! @_prodigy.tv  @officialteamrar @bagels_payne @andrew.bergh @matt_norloff @yea_drew @lizzycapri

I love to prove I can accomplish anything I put my mind to and prove people wrong. Even if that is to a build a giant remote control car, add rocket boosters, build a huge ramp, and jump the car 150ft in my backyard. Well with the help of all the insanely talented members of @officialteamrar we did just that and I was able to live my childhood dream of being like a mythbuster! This year I’m going to challenge myself to do the biggest and crazy things I can dream of. Off to a sting start. Part 1 of this video series is now live on YT!
Giant RC car jump part 1 is now live! Go@check it out on YT

It’s been a wild ride! I’m working on reinventing myself and doing bigger and better things

A lot more to come 💪

Just an awkward kid with a dream. This was the first time I ever saw a Lamborghini in my life (2014) 3 years before starting YouTube. I was excited to just see one and @lizzycapri took this pic. Little did I know I would own one of my one in just a few years. Now iv owned 4 lambos. The first one was the green sharerghini my brother @stephensharer and I bought together when we hit 1M subs on his channel. We spent every dollar we ever made to buy that car lol. Next was the red Lambo countach, I actually bought and sold 2 of them. And lastly is the Rarghini aventador. These are not materialistic items to me. Each one represents different stages and dreams coming true from years of hard work, risk,  sacrifices, and dedication paying off. Love all you guy who have supported me over the years 💚

Wow I’m speechless…. Today I woke up from a call from Andrew that I was 500 subs away from 10 Million subscribers. If I were to tell myself 6 years ago when I first started YT, I wouldn’t have believed it. It’s been such an incredible journey from quitting my job and having my boss tell me I was making a huge  mistake, and that I was destined for “greater things in life” then making YT videos with fidget spinners and nerf guns. Even after hitting 1 million subs I never though I would get to 10,000,000! 

Every step of the way iv had huge support from my family and friends and couldn’t have done it with out them all. My mom and dad, @stephensharer @stoves_kitchen @ryprunty @lizzycapri @bagels_payne @andrew.bergh @matt_norloff @yea_drew to name a few. I love everyone who has been apart of my journey and everyone who has watched and subbed!
